privacyPage.title: Privacy Policy
privacyPage.introText: This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, store, protect, and share your personal information through our services.
privacyPage.personalInfo: We collect the following personal information from you when you use our handicap tracking service:
privacyPage.infoItem1: Name and contact information, including email address
privacyPage.infoItem3: Golf-related information, including scores, handicap data, and course history
privacyPage.infoItem4: Device information and IP address when you access our service
privacyPage.infoItem5: Other information you choose to provide
privacyPage.automaticInfo: Information automatically collected when you use our service includes:
privacyPage.useInfo: We use your information for the following purposes:
privacyPage.useItem1: Provide and maintain our handicap tracking service
privacyPage.useItem2: Calculate and track your golf handicap according to official rules
privacyPage.useItem4: Communicate with you about your account and our service
privacyPage.useItem5: Ensure the security of our service and prevent fraud
privacyPage.sharingInfo: We may share your information with:
privacyPage.sharingItem1: Service providers who help us operate our platform
privacyPage.sharingItem2: Golf organizations as required for official handicap purposes
privacyPage.sharingItem3: Other users as part of the normal operation of the service
privacyPage.sharingItem4: Legal authorities when required by law or to protect rights
privacyPage.securityInfo: We implement appropriate security measures to protect your personal information from unauthorized access, alteration, or disclosure.
privacyPage.rightsInfo: You have rights regarding your personal information, including rights to access, correct, delete, and export your data. Contact us to exercise these rights.
privacyPage.changesInfo: We may update this Privacy Policy periodically. We will notify you of significant changes by posting the new policy on this page.
privacyPage.contactInfo: If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at privacy@openhandicapsystem.com.

termsPage.introText: These Terms of Service govern your use of the Open Handicap System platform. By accessing or using our service, you agree to be bound by these Terms.
termsPage.accountResponsibility: You are responsible for safeguarding your account and for all activities that occur under your account.
termsPage.accurateInfo: You must provide accurate, current, and complete information when creating an account.
termsPage.oneAccount: You may not create more than one account or transfer your account to another person.
termsPage.servicesText: Our service allows you to track and calculate your golf handicap according to the World Handicap System rules, manage your golf scores, and access golf course information.
termsPage.prohibitedText: You may not use our service for any illegal purpose or in violation of any local, state, national, or international law.
termsPage.prohibitedText2: You agree not to reproduce, duplicate, copy, sell, resell or exploit any portion of the Service without express written permission from us.
termsPage.terminationText: We may terminate or suspend your account and access to the Service immediately, without prior notice or liability, for any reason.
termsPage.changesText: We reserve the right to modify or replace these Terms at any time. If a revision is material, we will provide at least 30 days' notice prior to any new terms taking effect.
termsPage.contactInfo: If you have any questions about these Terms, please contact us at terms@openhandicapsystem.com.
